communication between officeholders and the people. The coming of
democracy in America owes much to the unprecedented energy with
which the petition was employed in the antebellum period. By
uncovering this neglected yet vital strand of nineteenth-century
life, Democracy by Petition will forever change how we
understand our political history.
},
